         <abstract>
            <p>A sharp inequality is proved about the product of some roots of a polynomial. It is used to bound the height of the factors of a polynomial. Applications are given to the problem of factorization and numerical examples show that these bounds strongly improve the previous ones.</p>
         </abstract>
